4x4 Unitary represents a 2-qubit system. Our decompose.py pipeline has to break thatcomplex 4x4 matrix down into a lot of simpler pieces. 
It goes from Two-Level matrices, to Controlled-U gates and finally down to Single-Qubit gates and CNOT.
By the time that breakdown is finished, a single 4x4 matrix has expanded into many individual Single-Qubit gates.
To convert those Single-Qubit gates into hardware H and T gates, our code uses a  linear search
It basically increments a counter (k) until the base rotation angle finally lands inside the tiny error window 
If we make the error tolerance ten times smaller, the code has to generate a string of H and T gates that is ten times longer just to hit that tiny target.
then if we combine these two things, the gate count explodes. If our 4x4 matrix decomposes into 30 Single-Qubit gates
and our strict error tolerance forces the brute-force search to spit out 500 H/T gates for each of them our final circuit is suddenly 15,000 gates long. 
